==Japanese==

===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|alt=其の}}
{{IPAfont|⟨so<sub>2</sub> no<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/sənə/}} → {{IPAchar|/sono/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|そ}}, distal demonstrative root, with {{ja-r|の}} added to form the ordinary adnominal form 'that', as in 'that word', as opposed to the pronoun {{ja-r|それ}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|acc=0|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Adnominal====
{{ja-pos|adnominal}}

# {{lb|ja|[[deictically]]}} [[that]] ... near you (near the addressee)
#: {{ja-usex|私が読みたい本は、'''その'''本です。|わたし が よみたい ほん は、 '''その''' ほん です。|What I want to read is '''that''' book.}}
# {{lb|ja|[[anaphorically]]}} [[the]] ... we are talking about.
# ...of it; [[its]]; [[their]]
#: {{ja-usex|'''その'''[[お姉さん]]|'''その''' おねえさん|'''her''' elder sister}}
#{{lb|ja|fiction|before a number}} {{n-g|indicates a part, chapter, volume, episode or installment; compare {{m|ja|編|tr=-hen}}, {{m|ja|話|tr=-wa}}, {{m|ja|巻|tr=-kan}}, {{m|ja|集|tr=-shū}}, {{m|ja|章|tr=-shō}}, {{m|ja|上|tr=jō}}, {{m|ja|中|tr=chū}} and {{m|ja|下|tr=ge}}}}
#:{{ja-x|日%本 映%画%論その三|^に%ほん ^えい%が%ろん その さん|Japanese Films: Part 3}}

=====Usage notes=====
* ''Sono'' is anaphorically used to refer to things and experiences that either the speaker or the listener knows about, but not both. Compare the two following sentences:
*: {{ja-usex|'''その'''本はやすいですか。|'''その''' ほん は やすい です か。|Is '''that''' book (which we are talking about) cheap? ''(anaphorically)''<br/>Is '''that''' book (I'm pointing to/near you/of yours) cheap? ''(deictically)''}}
*: {{ja-usex|[[あの]]本はやすいですか。|あの ほん は やすい です か。|Is the book (which we both know) cheap? ''(anaphorically)''<br/>Is that book (over there, which you and I can see) cheap? ''(deictically)''}}
* The hiragana spelling {{ja-l||その}} is preferred to the kanji spelling {{ja-l|其の}}, which is rarely used.

